54.4	Resident_Evil_(video_game)	Resident Evil (video game)	Resident Evil, known as Bio Hazard or Biohazard BaiohazƒÅdo) in Japan, is a survival horror video game by Capcom. The first installment in the Resident Evil series was originally released in 1996 for the PlayStation and was subsequently ported to the Sega Saturn and PC. In 2002, a remake of the game was released for the Nintendo GameCube featuring new graphics, voice acting and many gameplay changes. A Nintendo DS port of the original was released in 2006 titled Resident Evil: Deadly Silence.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/68/Resident_Evil_1_cover_art.jpg/250px-Resident_Evil_1_cover_art.jpg
